•Another remanded for raping teenager in Ekiti A 60-year-old man, Haruna Lawal, has been arrested by the police in Niger State for allegedly defiling an eight-year-old girl after luring her with N100.  This was as a Chief Magistrates’ Court in Ado-Ekiti, Ekiti State, yesterday remanded a 28-year-old man, Shola Oguntuase, for allegedly defiling a 14-year-old girl.  New Telegraph learnt that Lawal committed the crime on Saturday last week at Anguwan Barwa in the Wushishi Local Government Area of Niger State.  The sexagenarian reportedly lured the girl who was hawking fish into an uncompleted building where he had carnal knowledge of her.  The state Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), ASP Wasiu Abiodun, said the 60-year-old was a scavenger, who criminally took advantage of a minor and defiled her.  Abiodun said the suspect was arrested on a tip-off and that during interrogation, he confessed to have committed the crime.  The PPRO added that the suspect would be arraigned as soon as investigation was concluded.  Meanwhile, Oguntuase was remanded at the Correctional Centre in Ado-Ekiti. The defendant, of no fixed address, is standing trial on a one-count charge of rape.  The prosecutor, Inspector Oriyomi Akinwale, told the court that the defendant committed the offence on June 7 at Ire- Ekiti.  Akinwale said the defendant went to the house of the victim and defiled her. He added that the offence contravened Section 358 of the Criminal Code, Laws of Ekiti State, 2012.  The prosecutor urged the court to remand the defendant in the correctional centre pending legal advice from the office of the Director of Public Prosecution (DPP). The plea of the defendant was not taken.  However, the Chief Magistrate, Mrs. Olanike Adegoke, consequently adjourned the case till August 3 for mention. 